==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Collator
<hw>Col*la"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who collates manuscripts, books, etc.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>One who collates to a
benefice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who confers any benefit.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Feltham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Collaud</ent>⟦br⟧
